<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The Shame Paradox — Book Timeline</title>
<meta name="description" content="Follow the creation of The Shame Paradox: Why We Fear Most the Emotion That Keeps Us Human. A book by Nicole Chew-Helbig.">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600&family=Libre+Franklin:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;1,300;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

:root {
  --cream: #faf8f5;
  --taupe: #8b7b7b;
  --rose: #d9a7a0;
  --soft-pink: #f5e6e2;
  --charcoal: #2a2a2a;
  --accent: #a67c7c;
}

body {
  font-family: 'Libre Franklin', sans-serif;
  background-color: var(--cream);
  color: var(--charcoal);
  line-height: 1.6;
  overflow-x: hidden;
}

/* HEADER */
header {
  padding: 3rem 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(139, 123, 123, 0.15);
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 230, 226, 0.3) 0%, rgba(250, 248, 245, 1) 100%);
}

h1 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 3.5rem;
  font-weight: 400;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  color: var(--charcoal);
  line-height: 1.1;
}

.subtitle {
  font-family: 'Libre Franklin', sans-serif;
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--taupe);
  font-weight: 300;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.tagline {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--accent);
  font-style: italic;
  max-width: 600px;
  margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
}

/* TIMELINE CONTAINER */
.timeline-container {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 4rem 2rem;
  position: relative;
}

/* CENTER LINE */
.timeline-line {
  position: absolute;
  left: 50%;
  top: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  width: 2px;
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--rose), rgba(217, 167, 160, 0.2));
  transform: translateX(-50%);
}

/* TIMELINE ITEMS */
.timeline-item {
  margin-bottom: 4rem;
  opacity: 0;
  animation: fadeIn 0.8s ease-out forwards;
}

@keyframes fadeIn {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(20px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}

.timeline-item:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.1s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.5s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(6) { animation-delay: 0.6s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(7) { animation-delay: 0.7s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(8) { animation-delay: 0.8s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(9) { animation-delay: 0.9s; }
.timeline-item:nth-child(10) { animation-delay: 1s; }

/* ALTERNATE LEFT AND RIGHT */
.timeline-item:nth-child(odd) {
  padding-right: calc(50% + 40px);
}

.timeline-item:nth-child(even) {
  padding-left: calc(50% + 40px);
}

/* DOT */
.timeline-dot {
  position: absolute;
  left: 50%;
  top: 0;
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  background: var(--rose);
  border: 3px solid var(--cream);
  border-radius: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--rose);
  z-index: 10;
}

.timeline-item:nth-child(even) .timeline-dot {
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--rose);
}

/* CARD */
.timeline-card {
  background: white;
  padding: 1.8rem;
  border-radius: 2px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--rose);
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.timeline-card:hover {
  box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
}

.timeline-date {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  color: var(--rose);
  font-weight: 500;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

.timeline-title {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--charcoal);
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  font-weight: 500;
}

.timeline-description {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--taupe);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.timeline-status {
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
  border-radius: 20px;
  margin-top: 1rem;
}

.status-milestone {
  background: rgba(217, 167, 160, 0.2);
  color: var(--rose);
}

.status-current {
  background: rgba(166, 124, 124, 0.2);
  color: var(--accent);
}

.status-upcoming {
  background: rgba(245, 230, 226, 0.5);
  color: var(--taupe);
}

/* FOOTER NOTE */
.timeline-note {
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 5rem;
  padding-top: 3rem;
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(139, 123, 123, 0.15);
  color: var(--taupe);
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-style: italic;
}

/* CTA */
.cta-section {
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 4rem;
  padding: 3rem 2rem;
  background: rgba(217, 167, 160, 0.08);
  border-radius: 2px;
}

.cta-section h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  color: var(--charcoal);
  font-weight: 400;
}

.cta-section p {
  color: var(--taupe);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  max-width: 500px;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

.btn {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 0.9rem 2rem;
  background: var(--accent);
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  border-radius: 2px;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-family: 'Libre Franklin', sans-serif;
}

.btn:hover {
  background: var(--taupe);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  box-shadow: 0 6px 15px rgba(166, 124, 124, 0.2);
}

/* RESPONSIVE */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
  }

  .timeline-line {
    left: 0;
  }

  .timeline-item {
    padding-left: 50px !important;
    padding-right: 0 !important;
  }

  .timeline-dot {
    left: 0;
  }

  .timeline-card {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--rose);
  }
}

</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>The Shame Paradox</h1>
  <div class="subtitle">Why We Fear Most the Emotion That Keeps Us Human</div>
  <p class="tagline">Follow the creation of Nicole Chew-Helbig's groundbreaking book</p>
</header>

<div class="timeline-container">
  <div class="timeline-line"></div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 1 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">August 24, 2025</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">The Concept Begins</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        The central question forms: <em>"What if everything you know about shame is backwards?"</em> Nicole commits to exploring shame not as pathology but as the neural infrastructure of consciousness itself.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 2 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">August–September 2025</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Research & Framework</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        Intensive research phase. References compiled across neuroscience, philosophy (Buber, Naranjo, Simone Weil, Chödrön), clinical literature. The book's architecture takes shape: eight chapters weaving consciousness, relationship, neurobiology, and healing.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 3 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">September–October 2025</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Writing Begins: Part I</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        Chapter 1 (Eden) and Chapter 2 (Relationship) written. The philosophical and developmental foundations are established, grounded in clinical experience and personal narrative.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 4 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">October–December 2025</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Writing Continues: The Shadow Work</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        Chapters 5, 6, and 8 completed. The hardest chapters written: Humiliation, Shamelessness, and Therapy—threading the clinical case studies of Mark, Tina, and Clarke throughout to show shame's spiral and its healing.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 5 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">February 8, 2026</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Manuscript Structure Finalized</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        After months of refinement with developmental editing, the manuscript is reorganized into its final 8-chapter structure. Word count: 280–320 pages. The book is ready for submission.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 6 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">February 17, 2026</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Query Submissions to Agents</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        Manuscript submitted to eight literary agents including Emma Perry, Richard Pine, Kate Evans, and Natalie Edwards. The traditional publishing path begins.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 7 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">February 18, 2026</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">First Agent Response</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        Donya Dickerson at Aevitas Creative Management passes. Standard rejection. Waiting continues for responses from other agents.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-milestone">MILESTONE</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 8 -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">March 6, 2026</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Self-Publishing Decision</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        After reflection, Nicole decides on self-publishing through her imprint HELBIG. Faster to market, complete creative control, and the book speaks for itself. ISBNs pending from NLB.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-current">CURRENT</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 9 - UPCOMING -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">Mid-April 2026</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Feedback from Editor Karin</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        Manuscript returns from editor Karin with final copy-editing notes. Cover design finalized. Final revisions completed.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-upcoming">UPCOMING</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MILESTONE 10 - UPCOMING -->
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-card">
      <div class="timeline-date">May 2026</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Book Launch</div>
      <div class="timeline-description">
        <em>The Shame Paradox: Why We Fear Most the Emotion That Keeps Us Human</em> launches on KDP and IngramSpark. ISBN assigned. Available in print and digital formats worldwide.
      </div>
      <span class="timeline-status status-upcoming">UPCOMING</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<div class="cta-section">
  <h3>Stay Updated</h3>
  <p>Follow Nicole's work, clinical practice, and writing across her platforms.</p>
  <a href="https://nicolechewhelbig.com" class="btn">Visit Nicole's Site</a>
</div>

<footer class="timeline-note">
  <p>This timeline tracks the creation of <em>The Shame Paradox</em> from concept to publication. Updated as milestones unfold. Manuscript by Nicole Chew-Helbig. Self-published under HELBIG through FieldNotes Press.</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
